:19:02Z", "updated_at": "2016-01-08T20:03:17Z", "closed_at": "2016-01-08T20:03:17Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "The following code:\n\n``` rust\nfn main() {\n    println!(\"{}\", 1.2999999999999999);\n    println!(\"{:?}\", 1.2999999999999999);\n    println!(\"{:.3}\", 1.2999999999999999);\n    println!(\"{:.*}\", 5, 1.2999999999999999);\n\n    // aren't pretty too\n    println!(\"{:#}\", 1.2999999999999999);\n    println!(\"{:#?}\", 1.2999999999999999);\n}\n```\n\nprints:\n\n``` rust\n1.2999999999999998\n1.2999999999999998\n1.300\n1.30000\n1.2999999999999998\n1.2999999999999998\n```\n\nC behaviour:\n\n``` c\n#include <stdio.h>\nvoid main() {\n  double f = 1.2999999999999999999;\n  printf(\"%.14g\", f);\n}\n```\n\nprints:\n\n``` c\n1.3\n```\n\nWith Rust everything works like **f**, but not like **g**.\n\nIs that really no way to get behaviour like **g** option of `printf`?\nIt's highly important feature for serialization libs.\n\n_rustc 1.6.0-nightly (8ca0acc25 2015-10-28)_\n", "closed_by": {"login": "aturon", "id": 709807, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjcwOTgwNw==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/709807?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon", "html_url": "https://github.com/aturon", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/aturon/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://a